[[Skeletal Wyvern]]s are dangerous monsters, however they are very profitable to kill. The below lists show generally accepted strategies to defeat Skeletal Wyverns.

Note that a [[Slayer]] level of 72 is required in order to deal damage to Skeletal Wyverns. This may be boosted from level 67 Slayer by eating a [[wild pie]].

==Requirements==
*Level {{SCP|Slayer|72}} to deal damage against Skeletal Wyverns.
*Completion of {{SCP|Quest}} [[Elemental Workshop I]] or [[Elemental Workshop II|II]] for access to the [[Elemental shield|elemental]] or [[mind shield]] respectively. This shield offers protection to the very powerful icy breath attack of the Skeletal Wyverns.
**Alternatively, the [[dragonfire shield]], [[ancient wyvern shield]] and [[dragonfire ward]] also offer the same protection, all requiring having started [[Dragon Slayer I]].

===Recommendations===
*High [[combat]] stats. Although not required, see the skill levels below for an indication of the advised stats:
**If using [[Melee]]:
***Level {{SCP|Attack|75}} or higher
***Level {{SCP|Strength|75}} or higher
***Level {{SCP|Hitpoints|70}} or higher
***Level {{SCP|Prayer|70}} or higher for the [[Piety]] prayer
**If using [[Ranged]]:
***Level {{SCP|Ranged|70}} or higher
***Level {{SCP|Prayer|44}} or higher for the [[Eagle Eye]] prayer
**If using [[Magic]]:
***Level {{SCP|Magic|75}} or higher for the [[Fire Wave]] [[spell]]

==Getting there==
[[File:Wyvern runner routes.png|thumb|right|Getting to the wyverns.]]
The Skeletal Wyverns are located in the [[Asgarnian Ice Dungeon]]. The entrance to this dungeon may be found south of [[Port Sarim]] and north of [[Mudskipper Point]]. The quickest ways to travel here are:
#From [[Rimmington]] use the [[Teleport to House]] spell, a [[Rimmington teleport|Rimmington teleport tablet]], or [[Captain Barnaby]] and run south-east.
#From the Port Sarim docks using a [[Charter ship]], or the {{SCP|Minigame}} [[Pest control]] minigame teleport or [[Pest control teleport|scrolls]] and run west then south.
#From the fairy ring using code {{Fairycode|AIQ}} and run north.
#From Port Sarim using the [[Spirit tree]], [[Explorer's ring]], or via the {{SCP|Minigame}} [[Rat Pits|Port Sarim Rat Pits]] minigame teleport after the completion of [[Ratcatchers]] then run south-southwest.

From the dungeon entrance, climb down the trapdoor, first run north and then run east to find an open space with [[ice warrior]]s and [[ice giant]]s. The entrance to the Skeletal Wyverns can be found on the southern wall of this room. Players with level 72 [[Agility]] can take a shortcut right before the icy area.
[[File:Asgarnian Ice Dungeon map.png|thumb|left|A map of the dungeon where wyverns reside.]]
{{Clear}}

==Mechanics==
===Attack styles===
Skeletal wyverns attack with [[Melee]], [[Ranged]] and their unique ice breath attack.
*The Melee attack is only used when the player is standing in Melee distance and can hit up to 13.
*The Ranged attack has an attack range of 6 tiles and can hit up to 13.
*The ice-breath attack has an attack range of 5 tiles and can hit 50+, although this damage can be drastically reduced to a maximum hit of 10 by the following shields: [[elemental shield]], [[mind shield]], [[dragonfire shield]], [[ancient wyvern shield]] and [[dragonfire ward]].
**This attack will also freeze the player's character for a few seconds. During this period, the character is not able to move or attack.
***The [[ancient wyvern shield]] will grant an immunity against this freezing effect.
**[[Antifire potion]]s have '''no effect''' on the wyvern's ice breath attack.

===Draconic===
Skeletal Wyverns are considered to be [[Draconic (attribute)|draconic]] creatures, which means that they are weak against [[dragonbane weapons]].

==Tips==
===Dragonbane weapons===
Because Skeletal Wyverns are considered to be [[Draconic (attribute)|draconic]] creatures, they are weak against [[dragonbane weapons]]. Therefore it is recommended to use a [[dragon hunter crossbow]] or [[dragon hunter lance]] if any of these weapons are available.

===Safespotting===
[[File:Skeletal Wyvern southern safespot.png|thumb|300px|South of the cave door are some additional [[safespot]]s in which the western and southern sides of the ice structure (or pillar) can be used as safespots.]]
Skeletal Wyverns can be safespotted because they have a shorter attack range than players using a crossbow or magic spells. Skeletal Wyverns can be easily safespotted during a slayer task by standing near [[Steve]]/[[Pieve]]. 

#To safespot Skeletal Wyverns, first make sure to lose their [[aggressiveness]]. Aggressiveness is lost automatically after a player has spent 10 minutes in the same area (i.e. they don't move past a certain invisible border).
#After this time period, attack a Skeletal Wyvern and lure it behind an obstacle (e.g. a wall that is sticking out).
#While the Skeletal Wyvern is stuck behind the obstacle, move out of its attack range to make sure it can't attack the player anymore.
#Now start attacking the Skeletal Wyvern using [[Magic]] or [[Ranged]].

===Wyvern runners===
There are a few [[Clan Chat]]s with players that travel to different locations to deliver items to players who are training there.

When safespotting there, it is advisable to use these services to trade your unstackable lootings for new potions, runes or bolts.

===Dwarf multicannon===
[[Dwarf multicannon]] are allowed in the [[Asgarnian Ice Dungeon]], however only in the lower part of the cave; the upper Slayer-exclusive part is a no cannon zone. Cannons will make killing Skeletal Wyverns faster and the profit from the extra drops often outweigh the cost of the [[cannonball]]s. Therefore it can be recommended to bring a dwarf multicannon when meleeing Skeletal Wyverns.

